					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13953204#post-4852380</guid>
				<title>Twas the night before Christmas, and inside the shed, was a pile of upvotes, all stacked on a sled</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13953204/bring-me-flesh#post-4852380</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 24 Dec 2020 02:59:13 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Dr Kensing</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5941791</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The odd phrases in the parentheses adds the essential layer of surrealism to this, which is why I loved seeing this. I was already going to upvote when I was done reading, but the &quot;Naught but dust&quot; made me scroll up and give a +1. Normally, perspective tales on a hostile anomaly have a strangely-edgy atmosphere that I don't usually care for, but this one adds a well-crafted, alien-like mindset to the creature, and also does it <em>well.</em></p> <p>Edit: Also, throwing in &quot;Christmas&quot; as a catch-all word for the creature was extremely unsettling, and really gave the tale atmosphere.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
